<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[81648]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Manufactures Serra i Balet after the war]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Exhibitions.</strong> this exhibition of documents enables visitors to learn about the everyday life of a textile company in the district of Sants-Montjuïc during the Spanish post-war period.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>The company Serra i Balet was founded at the beginning of the 20th century and was involved in weaving, bleaching, dyeing and finishing corduroy. The Civil War led to the collectivization of the company. After the conflict ended, the repressive Franco regime purged the staff of the factory, a repression at both political, labour and cultural level. Lists of investigated and resigned workers, reports on the conduct of workers drawn up by the Falange Fascist Party, cultural events in praise of the new regime, etc.</p>
<p>The exhibition is based on text documents and photographs preserved at the Municipal Archive of the District of Sants-Montjuïc. They have been displayed for the first time giving an official and real view of the first post-war years in the city.</p>
